Subject: DevCollab - Hubot
Optional Attendees: Liudmil Petrov;James Kinneavy;Jeff Pignataro;Mark Norstedt;Joe Sabado;Stefan Chankov;Logan D Franken;Adriana Roman;Keith Jakobs;Joseph Chanson;Seth Northrop;Steven Maglio
Description:
Reserving the SIST Conference room. 
====
Hi Folks,


This is my first attempt at doing a devcollab session. Whats the topic? 

Well, a handful of folks have taken a strong interest in chat bots and the concept of ChatOps. James, for example, demoed a wonderful session on Microsofts bot framework and their natural language processing platform. James demo, which included the ability to request (in natural language) information about items in a database was impressive. That said, even though the demo was impressive, it was clear that Microsofts platform (currently in technology preview) is still undergoing some growing pains. Is there a chat bot framework out there that is already mature? yes! Hubot.

In this devcollab session, Ill take a look at hubot - the chat bot framework made available by the staff that work at GitHub. Ill go over the architecture, what advantages it brings, and also go into a high-level overview of how scripts are created and more. Im planning to have a demo of creating a new script to show a bit under the hood, but I also want to temper expectations a bit. The aim of this session will be to share basic to intermediate knowledge  not to show off. Certainly, Im a bit reluctant to show my own ugly code :). 

Anyway, Im hoping that folks that join in the call will take steps after to follow-up on the knowledge learned. Id love to be able to join a brainstorming session with a handful of others after this session to innovate on existing processes or improve on functionality.


Best,


Allen

Subject: IT cloud
Description:
Please join us for an afternoon of an exclusive IT presentation with one of our industry leaders on April 13th at 1:30PM at the Pavilion in the new UCSB Club. 
 
This is a free event, but there is limited seating, so I'll need people to reserve a spot through Evenbrite:
https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ucsb-it-presentation-backup-and-cloud-archive-featuring-rawlinson-rivera-tickets-32518551864 <https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eventbrite.com%2Fe%2Fucsb-it-presentation-backup-and-cloud-archive-featuring-rawlinson-rivera-tickets-32518551864&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNENkaIG5DTI7DsKt3LDTMx_zAEW3w> 
There is no charge, just click Register and fill in your info. 
--
Rawlinson Rivera will be presenting on Cohesity. Cohesity is a product that both extends secondary storage to the cloud and is a backup solution that archives backups to the cloud solution of your choice. There are other inviting features of Cohesity but I'll leave that to the sales guys.
Rawlinson has just come from VMware and will have lots of insight into the state of hybrid clouds, secondary storage, and leveraging the cloud in IT today. 
This is a great opportunity for us to ask questions about anything virtual and cloud based. This isn't just about one solution, this is a chance for us to get together and discuss and learn. 
Please let me know if you have any questions
 
Cheers!
Mike Franklin
805-893-5555
Location: Pavilion in the new UCSB Club.

Activity description: If you have been looking for a short, meaningful and effective introduction to evidence based mindfulness and meditation, this 4-week Mindful UCSB workshop is for you. During this workshop you will explore personal access points to developing greater mindfulness in your life. Through periods of silent mindfulness meditation, didactical instruction, personal inquiry, expert teachings, exercises and live Q&A, you will be skillfully guided to take your first steps with evidence based mindfulness practice.
